description.value: The DK MedCom Carecommunication IG

valueMarkdown.value: Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on HL7 Terminology

description.value: Care related communication between two or more parties in Danish healthcare

name.value: An identifier for an attachment.

description.value: An unique identifier for an attachment used in a CareCommunication message

The CareCommunication is used to ensure secure electronic communication of personally identifiable information and is most often used for ad hoc communication between parties in Danish Healthcare. However, the CareCommunication shall only be used in areas where no other MedCom standard is available, and it must not be used for cases with an acute nature.
Message header for care communication message
An extension holding an attachment identifier
Extension to contain the contact information tha author of the payload
Reference to author of this payload
Date and time of this payload
Reference to a more specfic sender of a CareCommunication message.
